Will leave more in depth review once I play, but I can already tell I will love it. I looked for new games the other night and this wasn't up. I never see your games for half off, no matter how often I check. Male lions tend to be pretty slim. Tinting Controls don't really work. Can't pinpoint a color without taking forever and going super slowly. Swiping the color wheel makes it change in a flash then go to black. Great sound effects and graphics! The varied minimap makes me excited to go exploring. The presence of flies is a fantastic realistic touch. Revised perfect pounce gets my adrenaline going! The night vision doesn't help. It's just green, not thermal. Random shadow grid glitches appear constantly in the world. Call me weird, but after seeing so many NatGeo specials, it's odd to see a male lion without testicles, haha.  I think you should make an ultimate cheetah simulator. When your animal gets close to starving, they should look emaciated. Fact #5 says, "from they preys stomachs."
